   Shirley was best known for her appearance in the James Bond franchise, but she also had a number of roles in the early Carry On films. The star chose to retire from acting in 1969 in order to bring up her family, but briefly came out of retirement in 1999 to release her autobiography titled Golden Girl, which was a bestseller. She was married to Colin Lenton Rowe from 1957 until his death in 1994 and the couple had two children, Grant and Jason. Some of the films Shirley appeared in before retiring include 1967’s The Million Eyes of Sumuru, 1959’s Carry on Nurse and 1958’s Carry on Sergeant.   